  "text": "Submaximal exercise systolic BP (ExSBP) is a better predictor of target-organ damage and cardiac mortality than office BP. [CITATION_1] The reason for this is unclear. If however the correlation between ExSBP and QT indices was stronger than that between resting BP and QT indices, then perhaps an increased arrhythmic risk associated with increased QT indices might offer a mechanism for exercise BP's superior prognostic value. In this crosssectional study, we explored whether there was a relationship between systolic BP measured during exercise and QT dispersion or QT c max.",
